                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                                        <date>1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> Feby /49</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Dear Friend—</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I have somewhat altered my mind as regards\n                                        the<lb/> article I lately sent you for the Occident. As I\n                                        have not heard from<lb/> you on this subject up to present\n                                        date, I conclude you intend publishing<lb/> it. I have\n                                        determined however, if you have not yet published it,\n                                        not<lb/> to let it remain as first written and therefore\n                                        must beg you to make<lb/> the following alterations in it\n                                        (i. e. if you want it). I was so bothered<lb/> when I sent\n                                        it you that I had but little time or attention to\n                                        bestow<lb/> on the Introductory observations (which alone\n                                        are not old papers, for<lb/> I believe I told you that the\n                                        quotation from Pentsal<add>?</add> with some, nearly<lb/>\n                                        all, indeed of the notes I had lying by for some time\n                                        waiting to be dressed<lb/> The <sic>consequense</sic> of my\n                                        writing hastily was as I afterwards recollected<lb/> that I\n                                        made a kind of promise to furnish several <add>?</add>\n                                        pieces, how<lb/> I shall be very happy to do so but I don't\n                                        want to bind myself to write<lb/> in any one particular\n                                        style or in any one particular subject, Hence<lb/> I now cry\n                                                  <add>?</add> and I want to alter my faux pas if it\n                                        be<lb/> one, in manner following. Problem. The\n                                                  Ed_<add>?</add> had an article on Hebrews<lb/> and\n                                        their opponents signed ADS, it is necessary to make an\n                                        alteration in<lb/> the same. If this be printed it is\n                                        required that it be printed as written from<lb/> the\n                                        commencement down till the end (in the Introductory remarks)\n                                        of <persName>Dr.<lb/> Mc Cauls</persName> vindication. After\n                                        the passage or sentence which commences “We leave<lb/> it\n                                        with the reader to determine how far <persName>Dr Mc\n                                                  Caul</persName> in the above extent<lb/> refutes\n                                        the <add>?</add> (I <sic>dont</sic> remember the exact words\n                                        as I didn't keep a<lb/> copy) insert this “With such\n                                        testimony, the testimony of an<lb/> adversary, it were\n                                        unnecessary (at this word insert at bottom the<lb/> note\n                                        which speaks<add>?</add> of translations of some Hebrew\n                                        authors already</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p30000g9m/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
