                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>writing such as the Hebrew Review Bible &amp;c Let the note begin\n                                        “Unnecessary<lb/> because the—) to produce in refutation\n                                                  <add>?</add> the good things they have written out\n                                        &amp;c &amp;c. Immediately<lb/> add at the end of this\n                                        sentence leaving out what I have already written<lb/> “But\n                                        perhaps it would be no improfitable <del>?</del> did the\n                                        contributors<lb/> to the Jewish periodical literature of the\n                                        day devote their attention<lb/> occasionally to these\n                                        charges which may almost be considered as<lb/> stereotyped,\n                                        since they are produced every day, in a new dress it\n                                        may<lb/> be, by those whose ignorance and prejudice will not\n                                        allow them to<lb/> know better. Leaving to other and abler\n                                        pens this (as we humbly<lb/> conceive) desirable occupation\n                                        we would <sic>commense</sic> the campaign of<lb/>\n                                        vindication by defending from severe and unmerited attack a\n                                        portion<lb/> of <hi rend=\"underline\">The Cosmography of R.\n                                                  Abraham Peitsal</hi><add>?</add> of which work as\n                                        a<lb/> whole we however offer no opinion, <del>as\n                                                  chiefly</del> because we are not called upon to do\n                                        &amp;c—<lb/> the charges against it being but partial; yet,\n                                        thus much we will say,<lb/> that books refer many reasons,\n                                        claims the most attentive and respectful<lb/> consideration\n                                        “of both the Jewish and Christian student” Then\n                                        continue<lb/> new Par. “This work thought not so well known\n                                        &amp;tc, and all the rest<lb/> as sent. (Q.E.D.) Now my dear\n                                        friend can I depend upon your<lb/> making these alterations\n                                        just as I have directed so that no inconsistency<lb/> or\n                                        contradiction exists in the article. I am sorry indeed to\n                                        prove<lb/> so troublesome a correspondent, but it\n                                                  <sic>canno</sic> be helped.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I told you we had formed a Sunday School here.\n                                        Perhaps you<lb/> would like a little information as to our\n                                        doings. I asked a meeting<lb/> at my <add>?</add> of the\n                                        ladies of the congregation, during <add>חנוכה</add>, when I\n                                        showed<lb/> them the necessity for some <add>?</add> being\n                                        made for the more efficient<lb/> religious instruction of\n                                        the young etc. In the usual course it was proposed<lb/> and\n                                        carried to establish a SS after the model of that\n                                        established<lb/> by the estimable <persName>Miss\n                                                  Gratz</persName> of your city. I was elected\n                                        superintendent<lb/> tho' I would have preferred that the\n                                        truth had been confided</p>"
                  },
