                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p30000g9m/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>to a <placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                                        <persName>Miss Gratz</persName>—but it was necessary I\n                                        should accept<lb/> and I did so. The young ladies of the\n                                        Cong. were elected teachers <del>and are</del><lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> to act when required. The present teachers are\n                                                  <persName>Miss Phoebe David</persName><lb/> who is\n                                        also secretary. <persName>Miss Rebekah Joseph</persName>,\n                                        and <persName>Miss Sarah Solomon</persName>.<lb/> The pupils\n                                        the first day were <del>27 an</del> 21 and have so\n                                        continued.<lb/> Books used—Pykes—Peichotto, and elder (boys)\n                                        Solomons Mosaic System<lb/> a copy of which was presented me\n                                        in <placeName>New York</placeName>. I need not add\n                                        further<lb/> particulars as these would be common to all\n                                        such schools.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am sorry to find you are not to inquire now of\n                                        the Proposed assembly<lb/> coming to something speedily. I\n                                        hope you are deceived <persName>J. H. Isaacs</persName>\n                                        letter<lb/> surprised me a little—he should not have\n                                                  <add>?</add> of difficulties and differences<lb/>\n                                        of opinion I still insist upon the <add>?</add> I forwarded\n                                        you being<lb/> correct that they will not be found in the\n                                        copy—and it is the fault<lb/> of the printers. I have yet a\n                                        copy of the article which I would send<lb/> if necessary.\n                                        The serious errors such as making the Jews settle in\n                                                  <placeName>Rome</placeName><add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        instead of <placeName>England</placeName> were I am quite\n                                        confident the faults of your barberous<lb/> named\n                                        compositors. I beg to acknowledge the Voice of Jacob\n                                        and<lb/> return you many thanks for your prompt attention to\n                                        my request. The<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> magazine has been discontinued and I hear it is\n                                        to reappear<lb/> in the reform interest. I know the two\n                                                  L<add>?</add>s and am not much<lb/> surprised by\n                                        this. Since <persName>Dr B</persName><add>?</add> retired\n                                        from the Editorship of the V_it<lb/> and its followers have\n                                        changed their colors like the chameleon.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I gave your receipts to the <persName>Messrs\n                                                  Benjamin</persName>. The think they<lb/>\n                                        <sic>dont</sic> owe so much but will refer to their books. I\n                                        will pay<lb/> over the money to your agent as soon as I can\n                                                  <add>?</add> it.<lb/> Of course you know that you\n                                        said agent is a Paper. <persName>Mrs J<lb/> H J</persName>\n                                        has a daughter. <persName>Mr J.</persName> altho' formerly\n                                        (i. e. before I came<lb/> out) one of the warmest &amp; best\n                                        supporters of the Synagogue, from<lb/> some reason or other,\n                                        cannot, unfortunately be persuaded to</p>"
                  },
